  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e618",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002d810",
    "text": "A filter passed in an invalid pre-operation callback status to FltCompletePendedPreOperation.\n(Filter = %p (%s), Status = 0x%x, Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e638",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002d920",
    "text": "A filter tried to complete pended callback data using FltCompletePendedPostOperation\nin the pre-operation processing phase. FltCompletePendedPreOperation should be used\nto continue processing of a callback data pended during pre-operation processing.\n(Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e648",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002da40",
    "text": "A filter tried to complete pended callback data using FltCompletePendedPreOperation\nin the post-operation processing phase. FltCompletePendedPostOperation should be\nused to continue processing of a callback data pended during post-operation processing.\n(Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e668",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002dbf0",
    "text": "A filter has set a completion context for a callback data which will be\nlost. Probable cause of this is that no post-operation callback was requested\nor routine was registered for this operation or the request was being pended\nor completed. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e688",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002dda0",
    "text": "A filter has marked a callback data dirty but is completing the request.\n(Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e6c8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002df30",
    "text": "A filter tried to complete a callback data but has returned STATUS_PENDING\nas the status in the iostatus block. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e708",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e240",
    "text": "A filter has changed the buffer during a pre operation callback but\nhas not registered a post operation callback and so will have no\nopportunity to free the buffer during completion\n(Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p, Source Instance = %p\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e738",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e3c0",
    "text": "A filter is calling FltDoCompletionProcessingWhenSafe when the callback\ndata is not in the post-processing phase. This routine can only be\ncalled from the post-operation routine. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e758",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e520",
    "text": "An attempt was made to issue IO on a file object which wasn't initialized.\n(FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e768",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e580",
    "text": "An attempt was made to issue an asynchronous IO on a file object which was\nopened for synchronous IO. (FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e778",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e600",
    "text": "An attempt was made to issue IO at a negative byte offset on a file object.\n(Filter = %p (%s), FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e788",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e680",
    "text": "An attempt was made to issue an asynchronous IO on a file object but no\nbyte offset was specified. (Filter = %p (%s), FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e798",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e710",
    "text": "An attempt was made to issue a non cached IO on a file object but the\nbuffer was not aligned. (Filter = %p (%s), FileObject = %p, Buffer = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e7a8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e7a0",
    "text": "An attempt was made to issue a non cached IO on a file object but the\nfile offset specified was invalid. (Filter = %p (%s), FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e7c8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e8a0",
    "text": "An attempt has been made to compare instances which does not belong to\nthe same volume. Such a compare is meaningless. (Instances %p & %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e7e8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002e9e0",
    "text": "An attempt was made to reference an invalid callback data. (Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e7f8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002ea30",
    "text": "An attempt was made to reference an invalid filter object. (Filter = %p).\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e808",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002ea80",
    "text": "An attempt was made to reference an invalid instance object. (Instance = %p).\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e818",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002ead0",
    "text": "An attempt was made to reference an invalid volume object. (Volume = %p).\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e828",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002eb20",
    "text": "A filter attempted to return MORE_PROCESSING_REQUIRED or call FltDoCompletionProcessingWhenSafe\nbut did not return pending from the pre-callback routine. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e838",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002ebe0",
    "text": "A filter attempted to complete an i/o via a pending i/o complete API for which this API is not\napplicable, as it is not an IRP operation. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e848",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002ec90",
    "text": "A filter is calling FltDoCompletionProcessingWhenSafe when the IO is \nbeing drained. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e858",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002ed10",
    "text": "A filter tried to disallow an IRP_MJ_SHUTDOWN, IRP_MJ_VOLUME_MOUNT,\n or IRP_MJ_VOLUME_DISMOUNT operation. (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e898",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002f1c0",
    "text": "Filter manager verifier object tracking may be out of sync for the system\nbecause the verifier was unable to identify the calling filter for %d object\nallocation(s)/reference(s) and for %d object deallocation(s)/release(s).\nFailure to identify the calling filter for an object allocation/reference\nmay cause verifier to complain when the object is freed/released even though\nthe filter is not performing any illegal operation.\n\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e8b8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002f520",
    "text": "Filter manager verifier object tracking may be out of sync for the system\nbecause the verifier was unable to identify the calling filter for %d object\nallocation(s)/reference(s) and for %d object deallocation(s)/release(s).\nFailure to identify the calling filter for an object deallocation/release\nmay cause verifier to complain when the filter is unloaded even though\nthe filter is not leaking any objects.\n\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e908",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002f950",
    "text": "For calls outside the context of a postoperation callback routine, consider using the\nFltReuseCallbackData and FltPerformSynchronousIo routines instead of\nusing the FltReissueSynchronousIo. (Filter = % p(% s), Cbd = % p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e928",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002fac0",
    "text": "A filter is trying to reissue synchronous IO for a create operation\nthat was cancelled (Filter = %p (%s), Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e938",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002fb40",
    "text": "A filter tried to cancel a file open for an unsuccessful open or after a handle \nis already created for the file. (Filter = %p (%s), FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e958",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002fc70",
    "text": "A filter changed the thread APC disable count across a call to its callback routine\n(Filter = %p (%s), Routine = %p, Cbd = %p, Count before = %s, Count after = %s)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e978",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x18002fe70",
    "text": "A filter changed the threads Special APC disable count across a call to its callback routine\n(Filter = %p (%s), Routine = %p, Cbd = %p, Count before = %s, Count after = %s)\nThis count is decremented each time a driver calls KeEnterGuardedRegion and\nis incremented each time a driver calls KeLeaveGuardedRegion.\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e998",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x1800300c0",
    "text": "A filter has completed an operation but does not implement name provider callbacks. For example\nif a filter completes an IRP_MJ_CREATE and is not a name provider it is possible that during name\nqueries the FO will make it's way to the file system and bugcheck. (Filter = %p, Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e9a8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x1800301e0",
    "text": "A filter has returned FLT_PREOP_COMPLETE but didn't update the IoStatus.Status field in the\ncallback data(Filter = %p, Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e9b8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x180030270",
    "text": "A filter has returned FLT_PREOP_COMPLETE but the IoStatus.Status field in the callback data\nwas set to STATUS_PENDING(Filter = %p, Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e9c8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x180030300",
    "text": "A filter has completed an operation but changed the TargetFileObject or the TargetInstance. This\nchange will be ignored and nobody above will see this. Please make sure the design doesn't rely\non this working!(Filter = %p, Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e9d8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x1800303f0",
    "text": "A filter tried to issue IO at an incorrect IRQL level, or with Special Kernel APCs disabled.\n(Filter = %p (%s), MajorCode = 0x%x, IsPaging = 0x%x, NonCached = 0x%x, IRP_MN_MDL = 0x%x, IRQL = 0x%x, Special Kernel APCs Disabled = 0x%x)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e9e8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x1800304e0",
    "text": "A filter called FltOplockFsctrl(Ex) for a create but the create didn't have either the\nFILE_RESERVE_OPFILTER or FILE_OPEN_REQUIRING_OPLOCK flags set.(Filter = %p, Cbd = %p)\n"
  },
  {
    "from_ea": "0x18003e9f8",
    "from_func": null,
    "string_ea": "0x180030590",
    "text": "A filter issued a create without setting the OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE attribute.\n(Filter = %p, (%s), Instance = %p, FileObject = %p)\n"
  },
  {
